{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844639182,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896b533001kKnhVBIaFRRMz8","messageID":"msg_d7896a6460013wdRguhaXlXr7l","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fc55188186064a9fae40b3e72e467c2f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"encoding/json\"\n6: \t\"fmt\"\n7: \t\"net/http\"\n8: \n9: \t\"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n10: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n11: )\n12: \n13: type Handler interface {\n14: \tRegister(r chi.Router)\n15: }\n16: \n17: type Logger interface {\n18: \tInfo(msg string, args ...any)\n19: \tError(msg string, args ...any)\n20: }\n21: \n22: type Store interface {\n23: \tStoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n24: \tGetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n25: \tUpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n26: \tDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n27: \tListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n28: }\n29: \n30: type ErrorResponse struct {\n31: \tCode    string `json:\"code\"`\n32: \tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n33: \tDetails any    `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n34: }\n35: \n36: type SuccessResponse struct {\n37: \tData any `json:\"data\"`\n38: }\n39: \n40: type ValidationError struct {\n41: \tField  string\n42: \tReason string\n43: }\n44: \n45: func (e *ValidationError) Error() string {\n46: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"validation error: %s - %s\", e.Field, e.Reason)\n47: }\n48: \n49: type NotFoundError struct {\n50: \tResource string\n51: \tName     string\n52: }\n53: \n54: func (e *NotFoundError) Error() string {\n55: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"not found: %s/%s\", e.Resource, e.Name)\n56: }\n57: \n58: type InternalError struct {\n59: \tErr error\n60: }\n61: \n62: func (e *InternalError) Error() string {\n63: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"internal error: %v\", e.Err)\n64: }\n65: \n66: type ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n67: \tDependency string\n68: }\n69: \n70: func (e *ServiceUnavailableError) Error() string {\n71: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"service unavailable: %s\", e.Dependency)\n72: }\n73: \n74: func HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, _ *http.Request, err error) {\n75: \tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n76: \n77: \tvar resp ErrorResponse\n78: \tvar status int\n79: \n80: \tswitch e := err.(type) {\n81: \tcase *ValidationError:\n82: \t\tstatus = http.StatusBadRequest\n83: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n84: \t\t\tCode:    \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n85: \t\t\tMessage: \"Invalid request parameter\",\n86: \t\t\tDetails: map[string]string{\"field\": e.Field, \"reason\": e.Reason},\n87: \t\t}\n88: \tcase *NotFoundError:\n89: \t\tstatus = http.StatusNotFound\n90: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n91: \t\t\tCode:    \"NOT_FOUND\",\n92: \t\t\tMessage: e.Error(),\n93: \t\t}\n94: \tcase *ServiceUnavailableError:\n95: \t\tstatus = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n96: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n97: \t\t\tCode:    \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\",\n98: \t\t\tMessage: e.Error(),\n99: \t\t}\n100: \tcase *InternalError:\n101: \t\tstatus = http.StatusInternalServerError\n102: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n103: \t\t\tCode:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n104: \t\t\tMessage: \"Unexpected server error\",\n105: \t\t}\n106: \tdefault:\n107: \t\tstatus = http.StatusInternalServerError\n108: \t\tresp = ErrorResponse{\n109: \t\t\tCode:    \"INTERNAL_ERROR\",\n110: \t\t\tMessage: \"Unexpected server error\",\n111: \t\t}\n112: \t}\n113: \n114: \tw.WriteHeader(status)\n115: \tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n116: }\n\n(End of file - total 116 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t\"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\ntype Handler interface {\n\tRegister(r chi.Router)\n}\n\ntype Logger interface {\n\tInfo(msg string, args ...any)\n\tError(msg string, args ...any)\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go","time":{"start":1775844639160,"end":1775844639181}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844639185,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896bd5c0014M3veOyOiKlq1U","messageID":"msg_d7896a6460013wdRguhaXlXr7l","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f656bca5cd864b02a1083ce73d1dc264","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement HTTP handlers for sandbox creation endpoints (`POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`) in the workload manager. These handlers convert user-provided AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRD references into actual Kubernetes Sandbox/SandboxClaim resources, orchestrate the creation lifecycle (wait for running status, resolve Pod IP, persist session metadata), and return session identifiers for downstream routing.\n6: \n7: Core responsibilities:\n8: 1. **Request Validation**: Parse and validate `CreateSandboxRequest` JSON (kind override, name/namespace required)\n9: 2. **Template Resolution**: Fetch AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter from client-go informer cache\n10: 3. **Sandbox Assembly**: Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload templates\n11: 4. **Creation Orchestration**: Register watcher, create CR, wait for running status (max 2 minutes)\n12: 5. **Post-Creation**: Resolve Pod IP, build entry points, persist to Store, respond to client\n13: 6. **Error Handling**: Rollback on timeout or failure (delete CR, remove Store placeholder)\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: ### In Scope\n18: \n19: | Deliverable | Description |\n20: |-------------|-------------|\n21: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate`, `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n22: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | Sandbox/SandboxClaim object construction from CRD templates |\n23: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | Creation orchestration: watcher registration, CR creation, timeout handling, rollback |\n24: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | client-go SharedInformerFactory integration for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter listers |\n25: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | SandboxReconciler with `WatchSandboxOnce` for status notifications |\n26: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | K8sClient wrapper: dynamic client, client-go typed client, pod informer |\n27: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: DefaultSandboxTTL, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout, label/annotation keys |\n28: | Test files | `*_test.go` for each source file (handlers, builder, creator, controller, client) |\n29: \n30: ### API Endpoints\n31: \n32: | Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n33: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n34: | POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | `handleAgentRuntimeCreate` | Create sandbox from AgentRuntime template |\n35: | POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` | Create sandbox from CodeInterpreter template |\n36: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n37: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n38: \n39: ### Out of Scope\n40: \n41: - Router deployment (`cmd/router`) and session routing logic\n42: - Agentd idle cleanup controller (`cmd/agentd`)\n43: - CRD type definitions (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`) — AR-001\n44: - client-go code generation — handled by `make gen-client`\n45: - Helm chart and deployment manifests\n46: - E2E integration test fixtures (handled in separate test task)\n47: \n48: ## Impact Analysis\n49: \n50: ### Upstream Dependencies\n51: \n52: | Dependency | Impact |\n53: |------------|--------|\n54: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Typed clients for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter; informers provide local cache; listers for read queries |\n55: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Create/delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs (external CRDs from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox`) |\n56: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Pod lister for IP resolution |\n57: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | SandboxReconciler watches Sandbox status changes |\n58: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Store interface for session persistence |\n59: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for API endpoints |\n60: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort) |\n61: | `pkg/common/types` | Shared types (CreateSandboxRequest, CreateSandboxResponse, SandboxInfo) |\n62: \n63: ### Downstream Consumers\n64: \n65: | Consumer | Usage |\n66: |----------|-------|\n67: | Router (`cmd/router`) | Uses `sessionId` from response to route HTTP traffic to sandbox Pod IP |\n68: | Agentd (`cmd/agentd`) | Reads Store records for idle/expired sandbox cleanup |\n69: | GC loop (`pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`) | Queries Store for inactive/expired sessions |\n70: | Auth middleware | Injects context keys (`userToken`, `namespace`, `serviceAccountName`) for per-user client |\n71: | E2E tests | Validates creation success, timeout rollback, error responses |\n72: | Helm chart | Configures `EnableAuth`, `EnableTLS`, `Port` flags affecting handler behavior |\n73: \n74: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n75: \n76: - **API Contract Stability**: Response schema (`CreateSandboxResponse`) must remain stable; adding fields is safe, removing fields breaks clients\n77: - **Timeout Constants**: `2-minute creation timeout` and `30-second delete timeout` are spec-required; changing these affects client retry behavior\n78: - **Session ID Format**: UUID format is documented; clients may parse/store it\n79: - **WarmPool Path**: `WarmPoolSize > 0` triggers SandboxClaim creation; changing this logic affects warm pool consumers\n80: - **Auth Integration**: Per-user dynamic client behavior when `EnableAuth=true` must match spec\n81: \n82: ## Alternatives Considered\n83: \n84: ### Alternative 1: Use Typed Sandbox Client Instead of Dynamic Client\n85: \n86: **Approach**: Generate typed client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs within agentcube's client-go.\n87: \n88: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n89: |--------|------------|\n90: | Pros | Type safety; IDE support; informer generation for Sandbox |\n91: | Cons | Sandbox/SandboxClaim belong to `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` (external dependency); adding to agentcube client-go creates maintenance burden; version mismatch risk |\n92: \n93: **Decision**: Rejected. Dynamic client with `unstructured.Unstructured` is the standard pattern for external CRDs.\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 2: Skip Store Placeholder Before CR Creation\n96: \n97: **Approach**: Create CR first, then store placeholder only after CR creation succeeds.\n98: \n99: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n100: |--------|------------|\n101: | Pros | Simpler flow; no rollback needed for Store if CR creation fails |\n102: | Cons | No idempotency check during creation window; GC cannot track in-progress creation; watcher registration before CR creates race condition risk |\n103: \n104: **Decision**: Rejected. Store placeholder before CR creation enables idempotency, GC awareness, and rollback target.\n105: \n106: ### Alternative 3: Poll Sandbox Status Instead of Watcher\n107: \n108: **Approach**: After CR creation, poll `GET` Sandbox status every 5 seconds until `running`.\n109: \n110: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n111: |--------|------------|\n112: | Pros | No reconciler dependency; simpler implementation |\n113: | Cons | Higher API load; potential missed events; less responsive (5s latency vs instant notification); wastes API quota |\n114: \n115: **Decision**: Rejected. `WatchSandboxOnce` via reconciler provides immediate notification and lower API load.\n116: \n117: ### Alternative 4: Separate Handlers for AgentRuntime vs CodeInterpreter\n118: \n119: **Approach**: Use distinct handler structs (`AgentRuntimeHandler`, `CodeInterpreterHandler`) instead of shared `handleDeleteSandbox`.\n120: \n121: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n122: |--------|------------|\n123: | Pros | Clearer separation; independent unit testing |\n124: | Cons | Duplicated delete logic; both endpoints use same session lookup; spec requires shared handler |\n125: \n126: **Decision**: Rejected. DELETE endpoints share identical session lookup and CR deletion logic per spec.\n127: \n128: ### Alternative 5: Embedded Template in Request Instead of CRD Reference\n129: \n130: **Approach**: Accept full PodSpec in request body instead of referencing existing AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter.\n131: \n132: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n133: |--------|------------|\n134: | Pros | No CRD lookup; simpler request validation |\n135: | Cons | No workload template management; no reusable definitions; larger request bodies; loses K8s-native resource model |\n136: \n137: **Decision**: Rejected. CRD references enable workload template management, RBAC per workload, and K8s-native integration.\n138: \n139: ## Risks\n140: \n141: | Risk | Mitigation |\n142: |------|------------|\n143: | Informer cache stale (AgentRuntime not found after creation) | Use `informer.WaitForCacheSync` at startup; fallback to direct API GET on cache miss (log warning) |\n144: | Watcher channel full (missed running notification) | Use buffered channel (size 1); non-blocking send with `default` branch logs warning |\n145: | Pod IP resolution fails (sandbox running but no PodIP) | Return error with rollback; Pod IP appears within seconds after Running phase—retry loop 3× with 5s interval |\n146: | Store unavailable during placeholder write | Ping store at startup; if Store fails during creation, return 503 (ServiceUnavailable) |\n147: | Timeout after CR creation but before rollback completes | Use independent 30s context for delete; log error if delete fails, rely on GC cleanup |\n148: | Concurrent creation for same workload (race condition) | Use Store placeholder as idempotency lock; check Store before creation |\n149: | Auth middleware context keys missing (EnableAuth=true) | Validate context keys exist before using per-user client; fallback to default client with warning |\n150: | WarmPool SandboxClaim vs Sandbox kind mismatch | Track `Kind` in `SandboxInfo`; delete handler switches GVR based on stored Kind |\n151: \n152: ## Implementation Notes\n153: \n154: 1. **client-go Integration Pattern**:\n155:    - `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` → `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Lister()`\n156:    - `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` → `Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Lister()`\n157:    - `clientset/versioned/fake.NewSimpleClientset()` for unit tests\n158: \n159: 2. **GVR Constants**:\n160:    ```go\n161:    AgentRuntimeGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}\n162:    CodeInterpreterGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}\n163:    SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\n164:    SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n165:    ```\n166: \n167: 3. **Watcher Registration Order**: Must call `WatchSandboxOnce` BEFORE `dynamicClient.Create` to avoid race condition.\n168: \n169: 4. **Timeout Configuration**:\n170:    - Sandbox creation wait: 2 minutes (spec-required)\n171:    - Rollback CR delete: 30 seconds\n172:    - GC single tick: 2 minutes\n173: \n174: 5. **Pod IP Resolution Strategy**:\n175:    - Primary: Pod name = sandbox name, read from `podLister`\n176:    - Annotation fallback: `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` annotation on Sandbox\n177:    - Label fallback: List pods by `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>`, match owner reference\n178: \n179: 6. **JSON Response Format**: Use `{\"message\": \"...\"}` for all error responses per spec.\n180: \n181: 7. **CodeInterpreter Defaults**:\n182:    - Empty `Ports`: Default to `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: HTTP, PathPrefix: \"/\"}]`\n183:    - Empty `AuthMode`: Default to `\"picod\"`\n184:    - `WarmPoolSize > 0`: Create SandboxClaim instead of Sandbox\n185: \n186: ## References\n187: \n188: - Spec: `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md`\n189: - Design: `sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md`\n190: - client-go Reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n191: - CRD Types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`, `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`\n192: - Shared Types: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go`\n193: - Project Context: `project.md`\n194: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n195: - agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n196: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n\n(End of file - total 196 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement HTTP handlers for sandbox creation endpoints (`POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`) in the workload manager. These handlers convert user-provided AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter CRD references into actual Kubernetes Sandbox/SandboxClaim resources, orchestrate the creation lifecycle (wait for running status, resolve Pod IP, persist session metadata), and return session identifiers for downstream routing.\n\nCore responsibilities:\n1. **Request Validation**: Parse and validate `CreateSandboxRequest` JSON (kind override, name/namespace required)\n2. **Template Resolution**: Fetch AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter from client-go informer cache\n3. **Sandbox Assembly**: Build Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload templates\n4. **Creation Orchestration**: Register watcher, create CR, wait for running status (max 2 minutes)\n5. **Post-Creation**: Resolve Pod IP, build entry points, persist to Store, respond to client\n6. **Error Handling**: Rollback on timeout or failure (delete CR, remove Store placeholder)\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775844639167,"end":1775844639183}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844639186,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896c15a001QlP8Lwk0E4vCjl","messageID":"msg_d7896a6460013wdRguhaXlXr7l","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-07d48633febd4c7e8d96205e05e321d5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [待填写] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: [待填写]\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** [待填写]\n20:   - [待填写]\n21:   - Verify: [待填写]\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## Task Dependencies\n26: \n27: ```\n28: [待填写]\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## Verification Commands\n34: \n35: | Task | Verification Command |\n36: |------|----------------------|\n37: | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## Acceptance Criteria\n42: \n43: - [ ] [待填写]\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## Files Modified/Created\n48: \n49: | File | Status | Description |\n50: |------|--------|-------------|\n51: | [待填写] | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Notes\n56: \n57: - [待填写]\n\n(End of file - total 57 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [待填写] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: [待填写]\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** [待填写]\n  - [待填写]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775844639169,"end":1775844639185}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844639191,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896b94c001DFZmfau7rot14M","messageID":"msg_d7896a6460013wdRguhaXlXr7l","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c36d6234041741d1acd79d81bb0964ad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package handlers\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"net/http\"\n5: \n6: \t\"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n7: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n8: )\n9: \n10: // HandlerFunc is a function that handles an HTTP request and may return an error.\n11: type HandlerFunc func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n12: \n13: // ServeHTTP implements http.Handler interface, calling the handler function\n14: // and handling any errors via workloadmanager.HandleError.\n15: func (hf HandlerFunc) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n16: \tif err := hf(w, r); err != nil {\n17: \t\tworkloadmanager.HandleError(w, r, err)\n18: \t}\n19: }\n20: \n21: // HandlerFuncAdapter wraps a HandlerFunc to make it implement workloadmanager.Handler.\n22: type HandlerFuncAdapter struct {\n23: \tPath string\n24: \tFunc HandlerFunc\n25: }\n26: \n27: // Register implements workloadmanager.Handler interface.\n28: func (h *HandlerFuncAdapter) Register(r chi.Router) {\n29: \tr.Get(h.Path, h.Func.ServeHTTP)\n30: }\n\n(End of file - total 30 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package handlers\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t\"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n)\n\n// HandlerFunc is a function that handles an HTTP request and may return an error.\ntype HandlerFunc func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error\n\n// ServeHTTP implements http.Handler interface, calling the handler function\n// and handling any errors via workloadmanager.HandleError.\nfunc (hf HandlerFunc) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tif err := hf(w, r); err != nil {\n\t\tworkloadmanager.HandleError(w, r, err)\n\t}\n}\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go","time":{"start":1775844639164,"end":1775844639189}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775844639206,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896c1d60016JyYWwjLMRp1J8","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7896a6460013wdRguhaXlXr7l","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":25107,"input":2095,"output":228,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":22784}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775844642020,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896cce1001pSDv7z97dSKxDH","messageID":"msg_d7896c205001I7eLreNGSSK4cZ","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844647295,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896dd870015RhaPLfoPyDD2f","messageID":"msg_d7896c205001I7eLreNGSSK4cZ","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bc39d93464d94f1f8b7d900505cdf481","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Orchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\n9: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n13: - **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n14: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\n17: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n20: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`\n21: - **WHEN** the template is deserialized\n22: - **THEN** `labels` and `annotations` are optional maps and `spec` is required and of type `corev1.PodSpec`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime status\n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with optional `conditions` of type `[]metav1.Condition`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Conditions optional\n28: - **GIVEN** a minimal `AgentRuntime` object\n29: - **WHEN** status is omitted or empty\n30: - **THEN** deserialization succeeds without requiring `conditions`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n33: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the same API group/version with subresource `status` and print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter GVR\n36: - **GIVEN** dynamic client configuration for workload templates\n37: - **WHEN** GVR is constructed for `codeinterpreters`\n38: - **THEN** group is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, resource `codeinterpreters`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with: optional `Ports` (`[]TargetPort`, JSON `ports`); required `Template` (`*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, JSON `template`); optional `SessionTimeout` with default `\"15m\"`; optional `MaxSessionDuration` with default `\"8h\"`; optional `WarmPoolSize` (`*int32`); optional `AuthMode` (`AuthModeType`, JSON `authMode`) with default `\"picod\"` and enum `picod` or `none`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Auth mode constants\n44: - **GIVEN** API constants for auth mode\n45: - **WHEN** `AuthMode` is compared\n46: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` equals `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` equals `\"none\"`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n49: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with optional `conditions` and optional boolean `ready`.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Ready flag\n52: - **GIVEN** a reconciled `CodeInterpreter`\n53: - **WHEN** status is updated by the controller\n54: - **THEN** `status.ready` may be set to `true` alongside a `Ready` condition\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: TargetPort and Protocol types\n57: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` with optional `pathPrefix`, optional `name`, required `port` (`uint32`), and required `protocol` (`ProtocolType`) with kubebuilder default `HTTP` and enum `HTTP` or `HTTPS`.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Protocol constants\n60: - **GIVEN** port configuration without explicit protocol in some code paths\n61: - **WHEN** defaults apply at API level\n62: - **THEN** default protocol is `HTTP` per kubebuilder marker\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Workload manager health endpoint\n65: The system SHALL serve `GET /health` without authentication and SHALL respond `200` with JSON body `{\"status\":\"healthy\"}`.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Health bypasses auth middleware\n68: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n69: - **WHEN** a client calls `GET /health` with no `Authorization` header\n70: - **THEN** the response status is 200 and body contains `\"status\":\"healthy\"`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Workload manager v1 routes and middleware\n73: The system SHALL mount a `/v1` route group with `loggingMiddleware` then `authMiddleware` (order preserved), and SHALL register `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Session id path parameter\n76: - **GIVEN** a delete request\n77: - **WHEN** Gin binds the path\n78: - **THEN** the session identifier is read from parameter name `sessionId` (camelCase)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Create sandbox request validation\n81: The system SHALL accept JSON for create endpoints matching `CreateSandboxRequest` with fields `kind`, `name`, `namespace`; SHALL overwrite `kind` from the handler (`AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter`); and SHALL reject requests where `kind` is not one of those, `namespace` is empty, or `name` is empty.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Validation failure returns 400\n84: - **GIVEN** the handler sets `sandboxReq.Kind` from the route and `Validate()` is called\n85: - **WHEN** `namespace` or `name` is empty in the JSON body\n86: - **THEN** the response is 400 and the error message includes `required` (e.g. `namespace is required` or `name is required`)\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create sandbox success response\n89: On successful creation the system SHALL respond `200` with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing `sessionId`, `sandboxId`, `sandboxName`, and `entryPoints` (each entry point has `path`, `protocol`, `endpoint`).\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Entry points reflect TargetPort and pod IP\n92: - **GIVEN** a sandbox reaches running state and pod IP is resolved\n93: - **WHEN** the response is built\n94: - **THEN** each entry point `endpoint` is `host:port` joined from pod IP and configured port, with protocol string from `TargetPort.Protocol`\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Create sandbox error responses\n97: The system SHALL return `400` with `{\"message\":...}` for invalid JSON or validation failure; `404` with message from wrapped not-found errors when AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is missing from informer cache; `401` with message from client extraction error when `EnableAuth` is true; `500` with `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}` for other create failures including timeout.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: JSON parse failure\n100: - **GIVEN** a non-JSON body to `POST /v1/agent-runtime`\n101: - **WHEN** the handler binds JSON\n102: - **THEN** status is 400 and message is `Invalid request body`\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Optional Bearer authentication via TokenReview\n105: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` with exactly two space-separated fields; SHALL validate via `authentication/v1` `TokenReview` create; SHALL cache results in an LRU cache (capacity 1000, entry TTL 5 minutes); and SHALL store in context: token, full username, service account name, namespace parsed from `system:serviceaccount:<ns>:<name>`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Missing header\n108: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n109: - **WHEN** `/v1/...` is called without `Authorization`\n110: - **THEN** response is 401 with message `Missing authorization header` and handler chain aborts\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: TokenReview success path\n113: - **GIVEN** a valid service account token and `EnableAuth` true\n114: - **WHEN** `validateServiceAccountToken` runs with cache miss\n115: - **THEN** the server creates `TokenReview` with `spec.token` set and uses `status.user.username` when `status.authenticated` is true\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Authenticated Kubernetes operations use user client\n118: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL use a per-user dynamic client (from bearer token) for creating/deleting `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` resources; when false, SHALL use the manager’s in-cluster/default dynamic client.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: User client cache key\n121: - **GIVEN** repeated requests from the same namespace and service account name\n122: - **WHEN** `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient` is used\n123: - **THEN** the cache key is `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation ordering and store placeholder\n126: The system SHALL call `StoreSandbox` with a placeholder `SandboxInfo` before creating the `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` in the API; SHALL register a one-shot watcher before create; SHALL wait up to 2 minutes for sandbox status `running` from the reconciler; SHALL resolve pod IP and then `UpdateSandbox` with full info; and SHALL roll back the created CR on failure after the wait (delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim within a 30s timeout context).\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Watcher registration before create\n129: - **GIVEN** a create request reaches `createSandbox`\n130: - **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is created\n131: - **THEN** `WatchSandboxOnce` was already invoked for that namespace/name\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Timeout returns error\n134: - **GIVEN** no running notification within 2 minutes\n135: - **WHEN** the select completes\n136: - **THEN** creation fails with error `sandbox creation timed out` and HTTP 500 is returned to the client\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: Pod IP resolution\n139: The system SHALL prefer pod name equal to sandbox name; if annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` exists on the created Sandbox (from agent-sandbox controller), SHALL use that as pod name; SHALL load pod from informer cache and require `PodRunning` and non-empty `PodIP`; otherwise SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>` and pick the pod whose controller owner reference is kind `Sandbox` and name matches.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Pod not running yields error\n142: - **GIVEN** a matching pod in non-Running phase\n143: - **WHEN** IP is resolved\n144: - **THEN** resolution fails with an error indicating the pod is not running\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: Delete sandbox by session\n147: The system SHALL load session from store by `sessionId`; on `ErrNotFound` return `404` with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`; delete `SandboxClaim` when stored `Kind` is `SandboxClaim`, else delete `Sandbox`; treat API `NotFound` on delete as success; then `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`; success response `200` `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`.\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Store miss\n150: - **GIVEN** no session key in store\n151: - **WHEN** DELETE is invoked\n152: - **THEN** HTTP status is 404 and message mentions the session id\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: Garbage collection loop\n155: The system SHALL run a background goroutine tick every 15 seconds; each tick SHALL use a context timeout of 2 minutes; SHALL query inactive sessions with cutoff `now - 15m` and batch limit 16; SHALL query expired sessions with `before = now` and batch limit 16; SHALL merge lists and delete each unique workload then remove store entry by session ID.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: GC uses DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout\n158: - **GIVEN** GC lists inactive sandboxes\n159: - **WHEN** computing the inactive cutoff\n160: - **THEN** `inactiveTime` equals `time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)` where `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` is 15 minutes\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: HTTP server and process behavior\n163: The system SHALL use Gin with `gin.New()` for the workload API; SHALL serve with `h2c` wrapping and `http2.Server`; SHALL use `ReadTimeout` 15s and `IdleTimeout` 90s for HTTP when not using TLS; SHALL ping the store before listening; SHALL sync informers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod) with up to 1 minute wait; on SIGINT/SIGTERM SHALL shutdown HTTP within 15s, cancel context, wait for background workers, then `Close()` the store.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: TLS requires cert and key\n166: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` is true and cert or key path is empty\n167: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n168: - **THEN** it returns an error that TLS is enabled but cert/key not provided\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: API error helper constants\n171: The system SHALL define in package `api` the sentinel errors `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound`, `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound`, `ErrTemplateMissing`, `ErrPublicKeyMissing`, and SHALL map `CodeInterpreter` kind to group-resource `agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` and default kinds to `agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` for `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError`.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Session not found uses API machinery\n174: - **GIVEN** `NewSessionNotFoundError(\"sid\")`\n175: - **WHEN** the error is inspected as `APIStatus`\n176: - **THEN** the group resource is `agentcube.volcano.sh, Resource=sessions` and name is the session id\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n\n## Purpose\nOrchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\nThe system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n\n#### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n- **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md","time":{"start":1775844647283,"end":1775844647293}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844647298,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896d9340018LXKJeN6e4brQR","messageID":"msg_d7896c205001I7eLreNGSSK4cZ","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-189ac6cb180b4398828879b0c2f7f17b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"fmt\"\n6: \t\"sync\"\n7: \n8: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n9: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n10: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n11: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/informers\"\n12: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n13: \tcorev1listers \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n14: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n15: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache\"\n16: )\n17: \n18: type K8sClient struct {\n19: \tdynamicClient   dynamic.Interface\n20: \tcoreClient      kubernetes.Interface\n21: \tinformerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n22: \tpodLister       corev1listers.PodLister\n23: \tpodInformer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n24: \tscheme          *runtime.Scheme\n25: }\n26: \n27: type ClientCache struct {\n28: \tmu      sync.RWMutex\n29: \tclients map[string]dynamic.Interface\n30: }\n31: \n32: func NewClientCache() *ClientCache {\n33: \treturn &ClientCache{\n34: \t\tclients: make(map[string]dynamic.Interface),\n35: \t}\n36: }\n37: \n38: func (c *ClientCache) GetOrCreateClient(token string, namespace string, config *rest.Config) (dynamic.Interface, error) {\n39: \tkey := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", token, namespace)\n40: \n41: \tc.mu.RLock()\n42: \tif client, exists := c.clients[key]; exists {\n43: \t\tc.mu.RUnlock()\n44: \t\treturn client, nil\n45: \t}\n46: \tc.mu.RUnlock()\n47: \n48: \tc.mu.Lock()\n49: \tdefer c.mu.Unlock()\n50: \n51: \tif client, exists := c.clients[key]; exists {\n52: \t\treturn client, nil\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \tuserConfig := rest.CopyConfig(config)\n56: \tuserConfig.BearerToken = token\n57: \n58: \tclient, err := dynamic.NewForConfig(userConfig)\n59: \tif err != nil {\n60: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create user dynamic client: %w\", err)\n61: \t}\n62: \n63: \tc.clients[key] = client\n64: \treturn client, nil\n65: }\n66: \n67: func NewK8sClient(config *rest.Config) (*K8sClient, error) {\n68: \tdynamicClient, err := dynamic.NewForConfig(config)\n69: \tif err != nil {\n70: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create dynamic client: %w\", err)\n71: \t}\n72: \n73: \tcoreClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n74: \tif err != nil {\n75: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create core client: %w\", err)\n76: \t}\n77: \n78: \tinformerFactory := informers.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(\n79: \t\tcoreClient,\n80: \t\tInformerSyncTimeout,\n81: \t)\n82: \n83: \tpodInformer := informerFactory.Core().V1().Pods().Informer()\n84: \tpodLister := informerFactory.Core().V1().Pods().Lister()\n85: \n86: \tscheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n87: \tif err := corev1.AddToScheme(scheme); err != nil {\n88: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to add corev1 to scheme: %w\", err)\n89: \t}\n90: \n91: \treturn &K8sClient{\n92: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n93: \t\tcoreClient:      coreClient,\n94: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n95: \t\tpodLister:       podLister,\n96: \t\tpodInformer:     podInformer,\n97: \t\tscheme:          scheme,\n98: \t}, nil\n99: }\n100: \n101: func (k *K8sClient) DynamicClient() dynamic.Interface {\n102: \treturn k.dynamicClient\n103: }\n104: \n105: func (k *K8sClient) CoreClient() kubernetes.Interface {\n106: \treturn k.coreClient\n107: }\n108: \n109: func (k *K8sClient) PodLister() corev1listers.PodLister {\n110: \treturn k.podLister\n111: }\n112: \n113: func (k *K8sClient) InformerFactory() informers.SharedInformerFactory {\n114: \treturn k.informerFactory\n115: }\n116: \n117: func (k *K8sClient) StartInformers(ctx context.Context) {\n118: \tk.informerFactory.Start(ctx.Done())\n119: }\n120: \n121: func (k *K8sClient) WaitForCacheSync(ctx context.Context) bool {\n122: \tsynced := k.informerFactory.WaitForCacheSync(ctx.Done())\n123: \tfor _, isSynced := range synced {\n124: \t\tif !isSynced {\n125: \t\t\treturn false\n126: \t\t}\n127: \t}\n128: \treturn true\n129: }\n\n(End of file - total 129 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"sync\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/informers\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\tcorev1listers \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache\"\n)\n\ntype K8sClient struct {\n\tdynamicClient   dynamic.Interface\n\tcoreClient      kubernetes.Interface","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go","time":{"start":1775844647281,"end":1775844647296}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844647300,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896e156001f1y8kFveteyfF9","messageID":"msg_d7896c205001I7eLreNGSSK4cZ","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3a821ffb2b3e405b9ff175efaec43f04","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/router.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/router.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import \"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n4: \n5: // Router wraps chi.Router to provide a simplified routing interface.\n6: type Router struct {\n7: \tchi.Router\n8: }\n9: \n10: // NewRouter creates a new Router instance with chi.NewRouter().\n11: func NewRouter() *Router {\n12: \tr := chi.NewRouter()\n13: \treturn &Router{Router: r}\n14: }\n15: \n16: // RegisterHandlers registers multiple handlers on the router.\n17: // Each handler's Register method is called to set up routes.\n18: func (r *Router) RegisterHandlers(handlerList ...Handler) {\n19: \tfor _, h := range handlerList {\n20: \t\th.Register(r.Router)\n21: \t}\n22: }\n\n(End of file - total 22 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport \"github.com/go-chi/chi/v5\"\n\n// Router wraps chi.Router to provide a simplified routing interface.\ntype Router struct {\n\tchi.Router\n}\n\n// NewRouter creates a new Router instance with chi.NewRouter().\nfunc NewRouter() *Router {\n\tr := chi.NewRouter()\n\treturn &Router{Router: r}\n}\n\n// RegisterHandlers registers multiple handlers on the router.\n// Each handler's Register method is called to set up routes.\nfunc (r *Router) RegisterHandlers(handlerList ...Handler) {\n\tfor _, h := range handlerList {\n\t\th.Register(r.Router)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/router.go","time":{"start":1775844647285,"end":1775844647298}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775844647328,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896e184001UKjL97BfJo3UQJ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7896c205001I7eLreNGSSK4cZ","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":30233,"input":5138,"output":217,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":24878}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775844652768,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7896f6df001ACxzE0UyFkibQ1","messageID":"msg_d7896e1bc001cPLQGS0an37wba","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844657601,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d78970108001AkE3J6AgTBwjQD","messageID":"msg_d7896e1bc001cPLQGS0an37wba","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4f02da4d001a4fa1ae9e3bc9b7d38b6f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Run a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\n9: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n12: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n13: - **WHEN** the manager is running\n14: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Idle detection input\n17: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n20: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`\n21: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n22: - **THEN** the sandbox is not deleted and result has zero `RequeueAfter`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Idle detection parsing\n25: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues\n28: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not RFC3339\n29: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n30: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiration threshold\n33: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n36: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n37: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n38: - **THEN** the controller calls delete on the `Sandbox` client object\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n41: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n42: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n43: - **THEN** the result is `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)` and no delete occurs\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Delete idempotency\n46: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox\n49: - **GIVEN** the API server returns not found on delete\n50: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n51: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Get not found\n54: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n57: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists\n58: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n59: - **THEN** reconcile returns without error\n60: \n61: ## Requirements (binary / operator)\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Manager options\n64: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n67: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n68: - **WHEN** SIGTERM/SIGINT is received\n69: - **THEN** the manager stops gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRun a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n- **WHEN** the manager is running\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n\n### Requirement: Idle detection input\nThe system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n\n#### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md","time":{"start":1775844657586,"end":1775844657600}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844657604,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d7897052b001RX76Q9uffV2fpM","messageID":"msg_d7896e1bc001cPLQGS0an37wba","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-588604540ee840bfbdbe4a3273da949e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"time\"\n5: \n6: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n7: )\n8: \n9: const (\n10: \tDefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n11: \tDefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n12: \tDefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\n13: \tDefaultSessionTimeout     = 15 * time.Minute\n14: \tSandboxCreationTimeout    = 2 * time.Minute\n15: \tSandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second\n16: \tInformerSyncTimeout       = 1 * time.Minute\n17: \tGarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute\n18: )\n19: \n20: const (\n21: \tLabelKeySessionID    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n22: \tLabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n23: \tLabelKeySandboxName  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n24: \tLabelKeyManagedBy    = \"managed-by\"\n25: \n26: \tAnnotationKeyIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n27: \tAnnotationKeyPodName     = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n28: )\n29: \n30: const (\n31: \tManagedByValue = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n32: )\n33: \n34: var (\n35: \tSandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n36: \t\tGroup:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n37: \t\tVersion:  \"v1alpha1\",\n38: \t\tResource: \"sandboxes\",\n39: \t}\n40: \n41: \tSandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n42: \t\tGroup:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n43: \t\tVersion:  \"v1alpha1\",\n44: \t\tResource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n45: \t}\n46: )\n47: \n48: const (\n49: \tSandboxKind      = \"Sandbox\"\n50: \tSandboxClaimKind = \"SandboxClaim\"\n51: )\n\n(End of file - total 51 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tDefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n\tDefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n\tDefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\n\tDefaultSessionTimeout     = 15 * time.Minute\n\tSandboxCreationTimeout    = 2 * time.Minute\n\tSandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second\n\tInformerSyncTimeout       = 1 * time.Minute\n\tGarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute\n)\n\nconst (","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go","time":{"start":1775844657590,"end":1775844657603}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844657606,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d78970996001rjCkfZ462Nzagn","messageID":"msg_d7896e1bc001cPLQGS0an37wba","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-af73f037488546789ecb108c755531eb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 为 WorkloadManager 构建 HTTP 服务框架，作为 agentcube 核心服务器的网络层基础，提供:\n6: \n7: 1. **RESTful API 基础设施**: 支持 Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session 等资源的 CRUD 操作\n8: 2. **中间件架构**: 提供请求日志、认证、限流、CORS 等可插拔能力\n9: 3. **生命周期管理**: 优雅启动、信号处理、连接清理\n10: 4. **可观测性**: 健康检查、就绪探针、Prometheus 指标端点\n11: 5. **错误处理**: 统一的错误响应格式与日志记录\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: ### In Scope\n16: \n17: | Deliverable | Description |\n18: |-------------|-------------|\n19: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTP 服务器核心实现，包括启动、关闭、配置 |\n20: | `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | 路由初始化与路由组管理 |\n21: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/base.go` | 基础 Handler 接口定义 |\n22: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | 健康检查与就绪探针实现 |\n23: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/logging.go` | 请求日志中间件 |\n24: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/recovery.go` | Panic 恢复中间件 |\n25: | `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/cors.go` | CORS 中间件（可选） |\n26: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | 请求/响应数据结构定义 |\n27: \n28: ### API Endpoints Framework\n29: \n30: ```\n31: /api/v1/\n32: ├── healthz          — 健康检查 (GET)\n33: ├── readyz           — 就绪探针 (GET)\n34: ├── sandboxes        — Sandbox CRUD (待后续 AR 实现)\n35: ├── sandboxclaims    — SandboxClaim CRUD (待后续 AR 实现)\n36: └── sessions         — Session 管理 (待后续 AR 实现)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### Out of Scope\n40: \n41: - 业务 Handler 实现（Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session）\n42: - WebSocket 路由与连接管理\n43: - 认证授权逻辑\n44: - 具体的限流策略实现\n45: - 数据库/存储层集成\n46: \n47: ## Impact Analysis\n48: \n49: ### Upstream Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Dependency | Impact |\n52: |------------|--------|\n53: | Go 标准库 `net/http` | 核心依赖 |\n54: | 可能的第三方路由库（如 chi, gorilla/mux） | 待设计决策，可选 |\n55: \n56: ### Downstream Consumers\n57: \n58: | Consumer | Usage |\n59: |----------|-------|\n60: | WorkloadManager 业务逻辑 | 通过 Handler 接口注册业务逻辑 |\n61: | 监控系统 | 通过 `/metrics` 端点采集指标 |\n62: | Kubernetes 探针 | 通过 `/healthz`, `/readyz` 检查服务状态 |\n63: | 客户端应用 | 通过 RESTful API 访问服务 |\n64: \n65: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n66: \n67: - **路由路径变更**: API 路径设计影响所有客户端\n68: - **错误格式变更**: 统一错误响应格式影响客户端错误处理逻辑\n69: - **中间件顺序**: 中间件执行顺序可能影响请求处理流程\n70: \n71: ## Alternatives Considered\n72: \n73: ### Alternative 1: 使用标准库 net/http\n74: \n75: **Approach**: 仅使用 `net/http` 标准库，手动实现路由与中间件。\n76: \n77: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n78: |--------|------------|\n79: | Pros | 无外部依赖；完全控制；性能最优 |\n80: | Cons | 路由功能有限；需要手动实现中间件链；缺乏社区生态 |\n81: \n82: **Decision**: 待评估。对于简单场景可行，但路由分组、路径参数等功能需要额外实现。\n83: \n84: ### Alternative 2: 使用 gorilla/mux\n85: \n86: **Approach**: 使用成熟的 `gorilla/mux` 路由库。\n87: \n88: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n89: |--------|------------|\n90: | Pros | 功能完善；社区活跃；中间件支持好 |\n91: | Cons | 外部依赖；性能略逊于 chi |\n92: \n93: **Decision**: 可选方案。\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 3: 使用 chi 路由器\n96: \n97: **Approach**: 使用轻量级 `chi` 路由器。\n98: \n99: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n100: |--------|------------|\n101: | Pros | 零依赖；性能优秀；兼容 net/http；内置中间件 |\n102: | Cons | 社区规模小于 gorilla/mux |\n103: \n104: **Decision**: 推荐。chi 轻量且符合 Go 惯例。\n105: \n106: ### Alternative 4: 使用 Gin/Echo 框架\n107: \n108: **Approach**: 使用完整 Web 框架（Gin 或 Echo）。\n109: \n110: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n111: |--------|------------|\n112: | Pros | 功能全面；性能优秀；生态丰富 |\n113: | Cons | 过度封装；违反 AgentCube 渐进式设计原则 |\n114: \n115: **Decision**: 拒绝。AgentCube 倾向于使用标准库 + 轻量级工具，而非重型框架。\n116: \n117: ## Risks\n118: \n119: | Risk | Mitigation |\n120: |------|------------|\n121: | 路由库选型错误 | 设计阶段充分评估 chi/gorilla/mux/stdlib，保留切换能力 |\n122: | 中间件顺序导致 Bug | 明确中间件执行顺序文档，添加集成测试 |\n123: | 错误响应格式不统一 | 定义 Error 结构体，所有 Handler 使用统一错误返回方法 |\n124: | 性能瓶颈 | 基准测试关键端点，监控 p99 延迟 |\n125: \n126: ## Implementation Notes\n127: \n128: 1. **配置**: 使用环境变量或配置文件指定端口、超时等参数\n129: 2. **日志**: 集成 pkg/logging，记录请求 ID、路径、状态码、延迟\n130: 3. **优雅关闭**: 监听 SIGTERM/SIGINT，等待现有连接完成（最长 30s）\n131: 4. **健康检查**: `/healthz` 总是返回 200，`/readyz` 检查依赖服务状态\n132: 5. **中间件模式**: 使用 Go 标准中间件签名 `func(http.Handler) http.Handler`\n133: \n134: ## References\n135: \n136: - Go net/http: https://pkg.go.dev/net/http\n137: - chi router: https://github.com/go-chi/chi\n138: - Kubernetes Healthz Pattern: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/configure-liveness-readiness-probes/\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 WorkloadManager 构建 HTTP 服务框架，作为 agentcube 核心服务器的网络层基础，提供:\n\n1. **RESTful API 基础设施**: 支持 Sandbox、SandboxClaim、Session 等资源的 CRUD 操作\n2. **中间件架构**: 提供请求日志、认证、限流、CORS 等可插拔能力\n3. **生命周期管理**: 优雅启动、信号处理、连接清理\n4. **可观测性**: 健康检查、就绪探针、Prometheus 指标端点\n5. **错误处理**: 统一的错误响应格式与日志记录\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | HTTP 服务器核心实现，包括启动、关闭、配置 |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/router.go` | 路由初始化与路由组管理 |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-004/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775844657592,"end":1775844657604}}}}
