{"type":"text","timestamp":1775844740876,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d78974b8200185dTp3vbIHlo5b","messageID":"msg_d7897275c001hovCd5K7rzhYDD","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the proposal.md for AR-006 based on my understanding of the codebase and requirements.","time":{"start":1775844740872,"end":1775844740872}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844740914,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d78984f0d001uCdGIeVZRwPO6h","messageID":"msg_d7897275c001hovCd5K7rzhYDD","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-38bd5366bb7041acac06cbb6c1224d9e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md","content":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement sandbox deletion handlers, garbage collection loop, and lifecycle management in the workload manager. This AR completes the sandbox lifecycle by adding:\n\n1. **Delete Handlers**: HTTP handlers for `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` that remove Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs and clean up session metadata from the Store\n\n2. **Garbage Collection Loop**: Background goroutine that periodically scans for expired and inactive sandboxes, deleting stale resources to prevent resource leaks\n\n3. **Graceful Shutdown**: Process lifecycle management with SIGINT/SIGTERM signal handling, HTTP server graceful shutdown, informer stop, and Store cleanup\n\nCore responsibilities:\n- **Session Lookup**: Retrieve `SandboxInfo` from Store by `sessionId`, return 404 if not found\n- **CR Deletion**: Delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim based on stored `Kind` field using dynamic client\n- **GC Loop**: Tick every 15 seconds, query expired sessions (TTL passed) and inactive sessions (idle timeout), batch delete up to 16 per tick\n- **Graceful Shutdown**: Cancel background workers, shutdown HTTP within 15s, close Store connections\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/delete.go` | HTTP delete handlers: `handleDeleteSandbox` for session-based sandbox deletion |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GC loop: tick-based scanning, expired/inactive detection, batch deletion |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | Process lifecycle: signal handling, graceful shutdown coordination |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` (update) | Integration: GC loop start, shutdown hook registration |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` (update) | Add `DeleteSandboxRequest`, `DeleteSandboxResponse` types if needed |\n| Test files | `*_test.go` for delete handlers, GC loop, lifecycle management |\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n| DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID (shared handler) |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Sandbox creation handlers (AR-005)\n- Router deployment (`cmd/router`) and session routing\n- Agentd idle cleanup controller (`cmd/agentd`)\n- CRD type definitions (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n- client-go code generation\n- Helm chart and deployment manifests\n- E2E integration test fixtures\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Impact |\n|------------|--------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Not directly used for delete; dynamic client handles Sandbox/SandboxClaim deletion |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs via `Delete` method with `metav1.DeleteOptions` |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | `IsNotFound` check for idempotent delete (treat NotFound as success) |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` (or Store interface) | `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListSandboxes` for session management |\n| `pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct with `Kind`, `ExpiresAt`, `LastActivity` fields |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | `DefaultSandboxTTL`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`, `SandboxDeleteTimeout`, `GarbageCollectorInterval` constants |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Router (`cmd/router`) | Session cleanup affects routing table; deleted sessions are removed from routing cache |\n| Agentd (`cmd/agentd`) | GC loop reduces load on idle cleanup controller; complementary cleanup mechanisms |\n| Monitoring systems | GC metrics: deleted count, cleanup latency, error rate |\n| Kubernetes cluster | Resource cleanup prevents orphaned Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs |\n| Auth middleware | Per-user dynamic client context (`EnableAuth=true`) affects delete operations |\n\n### Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Delete Response Format**: `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}` must remain stable\n- **404 Response Format**: `{\"message\":\"Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted\"}` format documented\n- **GC Constants**: `GarbageCollectorInterval = 2 minutes`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 minutes` are spec-required\n- **Kind Field Tracking**: `SandboxInfo.Kind` determines GVR for delete; must be populated correctly during creation (AR-005)\n- **Shutdown Timeout**: 15-second HTTP shutdown is spec-required\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Separate Delete Handlers per Kind\n\n**Approach**: Use distinct handlers for AgentRuntime vs CodeInterpreter delete endpoints.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Clearer separation; route-specific logging |\n| Cons | Duplicated session lookup logic; both use same Store and CR deletion; spec requires shared handler |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Both endpoints use identical session lookup and CR deletion logic. The `Kind` field in `SandboxInfo` already distinguishes Sandbox vs SandboxClaim.\n\n### Alternative 2: Polling GC Instead of Tick-Based\n\n**Approach**: Use Kubernetes informer events to trigger GC on Sandbox/SandboxClaim deletion.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Event-driven; immediate cleanup; lower latency |\n| Cons | Requires informer for external CRDs (Sandbox/SandboxClaim); GC also needs Store cleanup; event may miss Store-only entries |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Tick-based GC handles both CR cleanup and Store cleanup uniformly. Informer-based approach would require additional client-go code generation for external CRDs.\n\n### Alternative 3: Immediate Delete Without Store Cleanup\n\n**Approach**: Delete CR only; rely on Store TTL or separate cleanup process.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Faster delete handler; simpler implementation |\n| Cons | Store entries orphaned; GC would need to detect CR-missing entries; inconsistent state between Store and K8s |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Delete handler must clean both CR and Store for consistent state. This matches the creation pattern where Store placeholder is written before CR.\n\n### Alternative 4: GC Loop in Separate Process\n\n**Approach**: Run GC as a separate `cmd/gc` binary for dedicated cleanup.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Independent scaling; isolated failure domain |\n| Cons | Requires shared Store access; coordination complexity; spec requires GC in workload manager |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires GC loop in workload manager process. This enables coordinated shutdown and shared Store connection.\n\n### Alternative 5: Delete via controller-runtime Reconciler\n\n**Approach**: Use controller-runtime to watch Store entries and reconcile deletions.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Declarative pattern; automatic retry; status tracking |\n| Cons | Over-engineering for simple delete operation; Store is not a K8s resource; requires custom reconciler logic |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Direct HTTP handler + tick-based GC is simpler and matches the spec pattern.\n\n## Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Store unavailable during delete | Ping store at startup; return 503 on Store errors; GC retries on next tick |\n| CR deletion fails (network/API error) | Use 30s timeout context; log error; GC retries on next tick |\n| Race condition: GC deletes while user delete in progress | Store placeholder as lock; check CR existence before GC delete |\n| Session ID format mismatch (UUID vs custom) | Store lookup by exact key; validate UUID format in handler (optional) |\n| Graceful shutdown timeout exceeded | 15s HTTP shutdown; background workers get context cancellation; log if shutdown incomplete |\n| GC batch size too large (memory pressure) | Limit to 16 per tick per spec; log if more pending |\n| Informer cache stale for Pod lookup (if needed) | Not used in delete; GC uses Store timestamps only |\n| Per-user client context missing when `EnableAuth=true` | Validate context keys; fallback to default client with warning |\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Delete Handler Flow**:\n   ```\n   1. Extract sessionId from chi.URLParam\n   2. Store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionId)\n   3. If ErrNotFound → 404 response\n   4. Determine GVR: SandboxInfo.Kind == \"SandboxClaim\" → SandboxClaimGVR, else SandboxGVR\n   5. dynamicClient.Delete(ctx, GVR, namespace, sandboxName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n   6. If IsNotFound → treat as success (already deleted)\n   7. Store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionId)\n   8. Return 200 {\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}\n   ```\n\n2. **GC Loop Flow**:\n   ```\n   1. Tick every GarbageCollectorInterval (2 minutes per spec, 15s tick per another spec)\n   2. Context timeout 2 minutes per tick\n   3. Query inactive: cutoff = now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout (15m)\n   4. Query expired: cutoff = now (ExpiresAt < now)\n   5. Merge unique sessions, limit batch to 16\n   6. For each: delete CR → delete Store entry\n   7. Continue next tick\n   ```\n\n3. **Graceful Shutdown Flow**:\n   ```\n   1. Register signal handler (SIGINT, SIGTERM)\n   2. On signal: cancel main context\n   3. httpServer.Shutdown(ctx with 15s timeout)\n   4. Wait for background workers (GC loop, informers)\n   5. Store.Close()\n   6. Exit\n   ```\n\n4. **GVR Constants** (from defaults.go):\n   ```go\n   SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\n   SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n   ```\n\n5. **Timeout Configuration**:\n   ```go\n   SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second  // per CR delete\n   GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute   // GC tick interval\n   DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute  // inactive cutoff\n   DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour     // expiration cutoff\n   HTTPShutdownTimeout       = 15 * time.Second  // graceful shutdown\n   ```\n\n6. **Error Response Format**: All errors use `{\"message\": \"...\"}` per spec.\n\n7. **Idempotent Delete**: `IsNotFound` errors from K8s API are treated as success (sandbox already deleted).\n\n8. **Per-User Client**: When `EnableAuth=true`, use context-injected dynamic client; fallback to default client.\n\n## References\n\n- Spec: `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` (Delete sandbox by session, Garbage collection loop, HTTP server behavior)\n- Spec: `idle-cleanup/spec.md` (Idle detection pattern, SessionExpirationTimeout)\n- Design: `changes/AR-006/design.md`\n- client-go Reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n- Defaults: `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n- Store Interface: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` (Store interface)\n- SandboxInfo: `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`\n- AR-005 Proposal: `changes/AR-005/proposal.md` (Creation pattern, Kind field tracking)\n- Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n- agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go\">\nERROR [78:2] expected declaration, found informers\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":59,"character":40},"end":{"line":59,"character":71}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#omitzero"},"source":"omitzero","message":"Omitempty has no effect on nested struct fields"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":77,"character":1},"end":{"line":77,"character":1}},"severity":1,"source":"syntax","message":"expected declaration, found informers"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/handler.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/router.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775844740892,"end":1775844740911}}}}
