{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844746163,"sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","part":{"id":"prt_d78986390001HIA4ctN1iCiJLN","messageID":"msg_d78984f6a0016PoRco5souoQ2h","sessionID":"ses_28769c79dffe7cIjJ4VGEvPCLv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-768f342b631c407894669a99c541842b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement sandbox deletion handlers, garbage collection loop, and lifecycle management in the workload manager. This AR completes the sandbox lifecycle by adding:\n6: \n7: 1. **Delete Handlers**: HTTP handlers for `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` that remove Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs and clean up session metadata from the Store\n8: \n9: 2. **Garbage Collection Loop**: Background goroutine that periodically scans for expired and inactive sandboxes, deleting stale resources to prevent resource leaks\n10: \n11: 3. **Graceful Shutdown**: Process lifecycle management with SIGINT/SIGTERM signal handling, HTTP server graceful shutdown, informer stop, and Store cleanup\n12: \n13: Core responsibilities:\n14: - **Session Lookup**: Retrieve `SandboxInfo` from Store by `sessionId`, return 404 if not found\n15: - **CR Deletion**: Delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim based on stored `Kind` field using dynamic client\n16: - **GC Loop**: Tick every 15 seconds, query expired sessions (TTL passed) and inactive sessions (idle timeout), batch delete up to 16 per tick\n17: - **Graceful Shutdown**: Cancel background workers, shutdown HTTP within 15s, close Store connections\n18: \n19: ## Scope\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: | Deliverable | Description |\n24: |-------------|-------------|\n25: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/delete.go` | HTTP delete handlers: `handleDeleteSandbox` for session-based sandbox deletion |\n26: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GC loop: tick-based scanning, expired/inactive detection, batch deletion |\n27: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | Process lifecycle: signal handling, graceful shutdown coordination |\n28: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` (update) | Integration: GC loop start, shutdown hook registration |\n29: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` (update) | Add `DeleteSandboxRequest`, `DeleteSandboxResponse` types if needed |\n30: | Test files | `*_test.go` for delete handlers, GC loop, lifecycle management |\n31: \n32: ### API Endpoints\n33: \n34: | Method | Path | Handler | Description |\n35: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n36: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n37: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | `handleDeleteSandbox` | Delete sandbox by session ID (shared handler) |\n38: \n39: ### Out of Scope\n40: \n41: - Sandbox creation handlers (AR-005)\n42: - Router deployment (`cmd/router`) and session routing\n43: - Agentd idle cleanup controller (`cmd/agentd`)\n44: - CRD type definitions (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n45: - client-go code generation\n46: - Helm chart and deployment manifests\n47: - E2E integration test fixtures\n48: \n49: ## Impact Analysis\n50: \n51: ### Upstream Dependencies\n52: \n53: | Dependency | Impact |\n54: |------------|--------|\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Not directly used for delete; dynamic client handles Sandbox/SandboxClaim deletion |\n56: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs via `Delete` method with `metav1.DeleteOptions` |\n57: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | `IsNotFound` check for idempotent delete (treat NotFound as success) |\n58: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` (or Store interface) | `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListSandboxes` for session management |\n59: | `pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct with `Kind`, `ExpiresAt`, `LastActivity` fields |\n60: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | `DefaultSandboxTTL`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`, `SandboxDeleteTimeout`, `GarbageCollectorInterval` constants |\n61: \n62: ### Downstream Consumers\n63: \n64: | Consumer | Usage |\n65: |----------|-------|\n66: | Router (`cmd/router`) | Session cleanup affects routing table; deleted sessions are removed from routing cache |\n67: | Agentd (`cmd/agentd`) | GC loop reduces load on idle cleanup controller; complementary cleanup mechanisms |\n68: | Monitoring systems | GC metrics: deleted count, cleanup latency, error rate |\n69: | Kubernetes cluster | Resource cleanup prevents orphaned Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs |\n70: | Auth middleware | Per-user dynamic client context (`EnableAuth=true`) affects delete operations |\n71: \n72: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n73: \n74: - **Delete Response Format**: `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}` must remain stable\n75: - **404 Response Format**: `{\"message\":\"Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted\"}` format documented\n76: - **GC Constants**: `GarbageCollectorInterval = 2 minutes`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 minutes` are spec-required\n77: - **Kind Field Tracking**: `SandboxInfo.Kind` determines GVR for delete; must be populated correctly during creation (AR-005)\n78: - **Shutdown Timeout**: 15-second HTTP shutdown is spec-required\n79: \n80: ## Alternatives Considered\n81: \n82: ### Alternative 1: Separate Delete Handlers per Kind\n83: \n84: **Approach**: Use distinct handlers for AgentRuntime vs CodeInterpreter delete endpoints.\n85: \n86: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n87: |--------|------------|\n88: | Pros | Clearer separation; route-specific logging |\n89: | Cons | Duplicated session lookup logic; both use same Store and CR deletion; spec requires shared handler |\n90: \n91: **Decision**: Rejected. Both endpoints use identical session lookup and CR deletion logic. The `Kind` field in `SandboxInfo` already distinguishes Sandbox vs SandboxClaim.\n92: \n93: ### Alternative 2: Polling GC Instead of Tick-Based\n94: \n95: **Approach**: Use Kubernetes informer events to trigger GC on Sandbox/SandboxClaim deletion.\n96: \n97: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n98: |--------|------------|\n99: | Pros | Event-driven; immediate cleanup; lower latency |\n100: | Cons | Requires informer for external CRDs (Sandbox/SandboxClaim); GC also needs Store cleanup; event may miss Store-only entries |\n101: \n102: **Decision**: Rejected. Tick-based GC handles both CR cleanup and Store cleanup uniformly. Informer-based approach would require additional client-go code generation for external CRDs.\n103: \n104: ### Alternative 3: Immediate Delete Without Store Cleanup\n105: \n106: **Approach**: Delete CR only; rely on Store TTL or separate cleanup process.\n107: \n108: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n109: |--------|------------|\n110: | Pros | Faster delete handler; simpler implementation |\n111: | Cons | Store entries orphaned; GC would need to detect CR-missing entries; inconsistent state between Store and K8s |\n112: \n113: **Decision**: Rejected. Delete handler must clean both CR and Store for consistent state. This matches the creation pattern where Store placeholder is written before CR.\n114: \n115: ### Alternative 4: GC Loop in Separate Process\n116: \n117: **Approach**: Run GC as a separate `cmd/gc` binary for dedicated cleanup.\n118: \n119: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n120: |--------|------------|\n121: | Pros | Independent scaling; isolated failure domain |\n122: | Cons | Requires shared Store access; coordination complexity; spec requires GC in workload manager |\n123: \n124: **Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires GC loop in workload manager process. This enables coordinated shutdown and shared Store connection.\n125: \n126: ### Alternative 5: Delete via controller-runtime Reconciler\n127: \n128: **Approach**: Use controller-runtime to watch Store entries and reconcile deletions.\n129: \n130: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n131: |--------|------------|\n132: | Pros | Declarative pattern; automatic retry; status tracking |\n133: | Cons | Over-engineering for simple delete operation; Store is not a K8s resource; requires custom reconciler logic |\n134: \n135: **Decision**: Rejected. Direct HTTP handler + tick-based GC is simpler and matches the spec pattern.\n136: \n137: ## Risks\n138: \n139: | Risk | Mitigation |\n140: |------|------------|\n141: | Store unavailable during delete | Ping store at startup; return 503 on Store errors; GC retries on next tick |\n142: | CR deletion fails (network/API error) | Use 30s timeout context; log error; GC retries on next tick |\n143: | Race condition: GC deletes while user delete in progress | Store placeholder as lock; check CR existence before GC delete |\n144: | Session ID format mismatch (UUID vs custom) | Store lookup by exact key; validate UUID format in handler (optional) |\n145: | Graceful shutdown timeout exceeded | 15s HTTP shutdown; background workers get context cancellation; log if shutdown incomplete |\n146: | GC batch size too large (memory pressure) | Limit to 16 per tick per spec; log if more pending |\n147: | Informer cache stale for Pod lookup (if needed) | Not used in delete; GC uses Store timestamps only |\n148: | Per-user client context missing when `EnableAuth=true` | Validate context keys; fallback to default client with warning |\n149: \n150: ## Implementation Notes\n151: \n152: 1. **Delete Handler Flow**:\n153:    ```\n154:    1. Extract sessionId from chi.URLParam\n155:    2. Store.GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionId)\n156:    3. If ErrNotFound → 404 response\n157:    4. Determine GVR: SandboxInfo.Kind == \"SandboxClaim\" → SandboxClaimGVR, else SandboxGVR\n158:    5. dynamicClient.Delete(ctx, GVR, namespace, sandboxName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n159:    6. If IsNotFound → treat as success (already deleted)\n160:    7. Store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionId)\n161:    8. Return 200 {\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}\n162:    ```\n163: \n164: 2. **GC Loop Flow**:\n165:    ```\n166:    1. Tick every GarbageCollectorInterval (2 minutes per spec, 15s tick per another spec)\n167:    2. Context timeout 2 minutes per tick\n168:    3. Query inactive: cutoff = now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout (15m)\n169:    4. Query expired: cutoff = now (ExpiresAt < now)\n170:    5. Merge unique sessions, limit batch to 16\n171:    6. For each: delete CR → delete Store entry\n172:    7. Continue next tick\n173:    ```\n174: \n175: 3. **Graceful Shutdown Flow**:\n176:    ```\n177:    1. Register signal handler (SIGINT, SIGTERM)\n178:    2. On signal: cancel main context\n179:    3. httpServer.Shutdown(ctx with 15s timeout)\n180:    4. Wait for background workers (GC loop, informers)\n181:    5. Store.Close()\n182:    6. Exit\n183:    ```\n184: \n185: 4. **GVR Constants** (from defaults.go):\n186:    ```go\n187:    SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\n188:    SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n189:    ```\n190: \n191: 5. **Timeout Configuration**:\n192:    ```go\n193:    SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second  // per CR delete\n194:    GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute   // GC tick interval\n195:    DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute  // inactive cutoff\n196:    DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour     // expiration cutoff\n197:    HTTPShutdownTimeout       = 15 * time.Second  // graceful shutdown\n198:    ```\n199: \n200: 6. **Error Response Format**: All errors use `{\"message\": \"...\"}` per spec.\n201: \n202: 7. **Idempotent Delete**: `IsNotFound` errors from K8s API are treated as success (sandbox already deleted).\n203: \n204: 8. **Per-User Client**: When `EnableAuth=true`, use context-injected dynamic client; fallback to default client.\n205: \n206: ## References\n207: \n208: - Spec: `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` (Delete sandbox by session, Garbage collection loop, HTTP server behavior)\n209: - Spec: `idle-cleanup/spec.md` (Idle detection pattern, SessionExpirationTimeout)\n210: - Design: `changes/AR-006/design.md`\n211: - client-go Reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n212: - Defaults: `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n213: - Store Interface: `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` (Store interface)\n214: - SandboxInfo: `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`\n215: - AR-005 Proposal: `changes/AR-005/proposal.md` (Creation pattern, Kind field tracking)\n216: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n217: - agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 217 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement sandbox deletion handlers, garbage collection loop, and lifecycle management in the workload manager. This AR completes the sandbox lifecycle by adding:\n\n1. **Delete Handlers**: HTTP handlers for `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` that remove Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs and clean up session metadata from the Store\n\n2. **Garbage Collection Loop**: Background goroutine that periodically scans for expired and inactive sandboxes, deleting stale resources to prevent resource leaks\n\n3. **Graceful Shutdown**: Process lifecycle management with SIGINT/SIGTERM signal handling, HTTP server graceful shutdown, informer stop, and Store cleanup\n\nCore responsibilities:\n- **Session Lookup**: Retrieve `SandboxInfo` from Store by `sessionId`, return 404 if not found\n- **CR Deletion**: Delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim based on stored `Kind` field using dynamic client\n- **GC Loop**: Tick every 15 seconds, query expired sessions (TTL passed) and inactive sessions (idle timeout), batch delete up to 16 per tick\n- **Graceful Shutdown**: Cancel background workers, shutdown HTTP within 15s, close Store connections\n\n## Scope\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775844746153,"end":1775844746160}}}}
